title: [ICEs]: generic_const_exprs

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: S-has-mcve
labels.description: A Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example has been found for this issue

body:
### Code

```Rust
// ./tests/ui/inline-const/const-expr-generic-err2.rs

#![feature(inline_const)]

fn foo<T>() {
    let _ = [0u8; const { std::mem::size_of::<T>() }];
    //~^ ERROR: constant expression depends on a generic parameter
}

fn main() {
    foo::<i32>();
}
```


### Affected release channels

- [ ] Previous Stable
- [ ] Current Stable
- [ ] Current Beta
- [X] Current Nightly
